andromda_persistence:FinderMethod.andromda_hibernate_query: from FutureImpl f where f.securityFamily.id = :futureFamilyId and f.expiration >= :minExpirationDate order by f.expiration
select s from StrategyImpl as s where s.autoActivate = true order by s.id
from ForexImpl as f where f.baseCurrency = :baseCurrency and f.securityFamily.currency = :transactionCurrency
select distinct c from CombinationImpl as c join fetch c.master as m join fetch c.allocations join fetch c.strategy as s where s.name = :strategyName and m.class = :type
select s from StockOptionImpl as s join s.securityFamily as sf where sf.id = :securityFamilyId

select * from stock_option so inner join security s on s.id = so.id where s.underlaying_fk = :underlayingId and so.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate and if(so.type = 'PUT', so.strike, -so.strike) <= if(so.type = 'PUT', :underlayingSpot, -:underlayingSpot) and so.type = :optionTypeString order by so.expiration asc, if(so.type = 'PUT', -so.strike, so.strike) asc limit 1
select distinct c from CombinationImpl as c join fetch c.allocations join fetch c.strategy as s where s.name = :strategyName
from WatchListItemImpl where strategy.name = :strategyName order by security.id
from TickImpl as t join fetch t.security as s where t.dateTime = :date and s.underlaying = :underlaying and s.type = :type and s.expiration = :expiration order by s.strike

select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.securityFamily as f join fetch s.watchListItems as w left join fetch s.positions as p join fetch w.strategy as st where w.strategy.autoActivate = true order by s.id
from TransactionImpl as t where t.type = 'CREDIT' or t.type = 'DEBIT' or t.type = 'INTREST_PAID' or t.type = 'INTREST_RECEIVED' or t.type = 'FEES' or t.type = 'REFUND' order by t.id
select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.securityFamily as f join s.watchListItems as w where w != null order by s.id
select f from SecurityImpl as s join s.derivedSecurityFamilies as f where f.class = StockOptionFamilyImpl and s.id = :underlayingId
select s from StockOptionImpl as s left join fetch s.positions as p join s.watchListItems as w where w != null order by s.id
select * from future f inner join security s on s.id = f.id where s.security_family_fk = :futureFamilyId and f.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate order by f.expiration asc limit 1
select p from com.algoTrader.entity.security.Expirable as e join e.positions as p where p.quantity != 0 and e.expiration <= :currentTime
from TransactionImpl as t join fetch t.security where t.type = 'BUY' or t.type = 'SELL' or t.type = 'EXPIRATION' order by t.id
from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.security.id = :securityId and p.quantity != 0 order by p.id
select s from SecurityImpl as s join s.watchListItems as w where w != null and s.securityFamily.simulatable = true order by s.id
select f from FutureImpl as f join f.securityFamily as sf where sf.id = :securityFamilyId
select p from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.quantity != 0 order by p.id

select * from ( select * from tick where security_fk = :securityId order by date_time desc limit :n
) as t order by t.date_time asc
select s from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.securityFamily as f join s.watchListItems as w where w != null and f.periodicity = :periodicity order by s.id
select distinct c from CombinationImpl as c join fetch c.master as m join fetch c.allocations join fetch c.strategy where m.id = :masterSecurityId
from SecurityImpl as s where s.symbol = :symbol
select f from SecurityImpl as s join s.securityFamily as f where s.isin = :isin
from WatchListItemImpl where strategy.name = :strategyName and security.id = :securityId

select w from WatchListItemImpl as w join w.security as s where w.strategy.name = :strategyName and s not in ( select p.security from PositionImpl as p where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0) and s.class = :type
select * from tick as t where t.security_fk = :securityId and date_time <= :date and date_time > DATE_SUB(:date, INTERVAL 1 MINUTE) order by t.date_time limit 1
select t.id from ( select * from tick where security_fk = :securityId order by date_time desc limit :n ) as t order by t.date_time asc
from TickImpl as t left join fetch t.security as s left join fetch s.underlaying as ul left join fetch s.positions as p where t.id in (:ids) order by t.dateTime asc
from FutureImpl f where f.securityFamily.id = :futureFamilyId and f.expiration = :expirationDate
select distinct c from CombinationImpl as c join fetch c.master as m join fetch c.allocations as a join fetch c.strategy as s where s.name = :strategyName and m.class = :type and a.quantity = 0
select * from transaction order by date_time desc limit :maxResults
from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.underlaying as ul join fetch s.securityFamily as f where s.isin = :isin
from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0 order by p.id
from SecurityImpl as s where s.isin = :isin
select distinct s.expiration from TickImpl as t join t.security as s where t.dateTime = :dateTime and s.class = StockOptionImpl order by s.expiration

select t1.id from tick as t1 join (select max(id) as id from tick where date_time < :maxDate and security_fk = :securityId and time(date_time) < time(:time) group by date(date_time) ) as t2 on t1.id = t2.id order by t1.date_time asc
from WatchListItemImpl as w where w.persistent = false
from WatchListItemImpl as w where w.persistent = true
select distinct a from AllocationImpl as a join fetch a.security as s join fetch a.combination as c join fetch c.strategy as st where st.name = :strategyName
from SecurityImpl as s where s.id in (:ids) order by s.id
from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.strategy.name = :strategyName order by p.id
select distinct a from AllocationImpl as a join fetch a.security as s join fetch a.combination as c join fetch c.strategy as st where st.name = :strategyName and s.class = :type
select * from tick where security_fk = :securityId and date_time <= :maxDate order by date_time desc limit 1
select t from TickImpl as t join t.security.watchListItems as w where w != null and t.dateTime > :startDate and t.dateTime < :endDate order by t.dateTime
select distinct c from CombinationImpl as c join fetch c.master as m join fetch c.allocations join fetch c.strategy as s where s.name = :strategyName and m.id = :masterSecurityId
from WatchListItemImpl as w where w.strategy.name = :strategyName and w.security not in ( select p.security from PositionImpl as p where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0)
from StrategyImpl where name = :name
select p from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.quantity != 0 and s.class = ForexImpl order by p.id
select distinct c.currency from CashBalanceImpl as c
select distinct dateTime from TickImpl
select s from SecurityImpl as s join fetch s.positions as p where p.quantity != 0 order by s.id
from TickImpl as s where s.security.id = :securityId order by s.dateTime
from FutureImpl f where f.underlaying.id = :underlayingId and f.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate
select f from FutureImpl as f left join fetch f.positions as p join f.watchListItems as w where w != null order by f.id
select p from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f left join fetch s.underlaying as ul where p.id = :id
from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0 and s.class = ForexImpl order by p.id
select distinct c.currency from CashBalanceImpl as c left join c.strategy as s where or s.name = :strategyName
select p from PositionImpl as p where p.id = :id
from SecurityImpl as s where s.id = :id

select t1.id from tick as t1 join (select min(id) as id from tick where date_time < :maxDate and security_fk = :securityId and time(date_time) > time(:time) group by date(date_time) ) as t2 on t1.id = t2.id order by t1.date_time asc
select distinct a from AllocationImpl as a join fetch a.security as s join fetch a.combination as c join fetch c.strategy as st where st.name = :strategyName and s.id = :securityId
from StrategyImpl as st where st.name = :name
select t from ImpliedVolatilityImpl as i, TickImpl as t where t.security = i and t.dateTime = :date and i.underlaying = :underlaying and i.duration = :duration order by i.moneyness desc

select so.expiration from stock_option so join security s on s.id = so.id join tick as t on s.id = t.security_fk where s.underlaying_fk = :underlayingId and t.date_time = :date order by abs(datediff(so.expiration, :targetDate)) limit 1
select s from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.securityFamily as f join s.watchListItems as w where w != null and w.strategy.name = :strategyName order by s.id
select distinct c from CombinationImpl as c join fetch c.master join fetch c.allocations as a join fetch c.strategy as s where s.name = :strategyName and a.security.id = :securityId
from PositionImpl as p join fetch p.security as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f where p.security.id = :securityId and p.strategy.name = :strategyName
select * from transaction as t join strategy as s on s.id = t.strategy_fk where s.name = :strategyName order by t.date_time desc limit :maxResults
select f from SecurityImpl as s join s.derivedSecurityFamilies as f where f.class = FutureFamilyImpl and s.id = :underlayingId

select s.*, so.* from stock_option so inner join security s on s.id = so.id join tick as t on s.id = t.security_fk where s.underlaying_fk = :underlayingId and so.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate and if(so.type = 'PUT', so.strike, -so.strike) <= if(so.type = 'PUT', :underlayingSpot, -:underlayingSpot) and so.type = :optionTypeString and t.date_time = :date order by so.expiration asc, if(so.type = 'PUT', -so.strike, so.strike) asc limit 1
from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.underlaying as ul join fetch s.securityFamily as f where s.id = :id
